<br>
It's literally just as bright at night as it is during the day.  The sky darkens, but the ground continues to glow as if it's a light source of its own.  You can see perfectly, even as a human.<br>
Even moonlight isn't *that* bright!  <br>
It just looks... stupid.<br>
<br>
I think it completely ruins the feel of night time.  Not to mention that I ducked through the Oasis (which is still under control of the Sand Giants) to buy an infravision spell... for no reason!<br>
<br>
Golsec <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufritzdarkweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fritz Darkweaver</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wedgie Avenger</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/23/01 5:07:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=71.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: They nerfed nighttime!</span><hr size=1> Hrmm, I hadn't noticed.  But I can say that as a human I enjoyed having to work around the sight difficulties.  It made the game more challenging.<br>
